inflexible.d:
a. incapable of change
a. resistant to being bent; 
s. incapable of adapting or changing to meet circumstances

infold.d:
v. t. To wrap up or cover with folds; to envelop; to inwrap;
   to inclose; to involve.
v. t. To clasp with the arms; to embrace.

infundibuliform.d:
a. Having the form of a funnel or cone;
   funnel-shaped.
a. Same as Funnelform.

inofficial.d:
a. Not official; not having official sanction or authoriy;
   not according to the forms or ceremony of official business; as,
   inofficial intelligence.

institutionary.d:
a. Relating to an institution, or institutions.
a. Containing the first principles or doctrines;
   elemental; rudimentary.

insufferably.d:
adv. In a manner or to a degree beyond endurance;
   intolerably; as, a blaze insufferably bright; a person insufferably
   proud.

interlining.d:
p. pr. & vb. n. of Interline
n. Correction or alteration by writing between the lines;
   interlineation.

investigable.d:
a. Capable or susceptible of being investigated;
   admitting research.
a. Unsearchable; inscrutable.
